The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | DAY II HIGHLIGHTS
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Day II highlights
                      
	 On 100, Sourav Ganguly scored the 16th Test hundred of his career. It was also his second at Mohali, second vs Australia, eighth at home and 15th in the first innings.         
	 On 67, he bettered his previous best vs Australia at home. He had scored 66 against them in the first Gavaskar-Border Trophy match in 1996-97 in Delhi.         
	 On 68, Ganguly brought up 600 runs in 2008. He became the fifth Indian player to cross the mark this year after Virender Sehwag (1088), V.V.S. Laxman (694), Rahul Dravid (637), and Sachin Tendulkar (661).         
	 M.S. Dhoni registered his 10th Test fifty and his first as captain.         
	 On 87, Dhoni registered the highest score by any wicketkeeper captain from the subcontinent. Pakistans Imtiaz Ahmed had scored 86 vs England way back in 1961-62.         
	 Dhoni was dismissed for the second time in the 90s. Coincidentally, he was also dismissed on 92 vs England at the Oval in 2007.         
	 Zaheer Khan has now dismissed Mathew Hayden seven times (the maximum) in Test. The other bowlers also to dismiss Hayden seven times are Harbhajan Singh and Makhaya Ntini.         
	 Ishant Sharma has now dismissed Ricky Ponting four times. They have played against each other in 5 Tests now. However, it was the first time Ponting was dismissed lbw by Sharma. On all previous occasions, he was caught.                         [+uc(' COMPILED BY MOHANDAS MENON   ')+]                                                                                                                      
